summary: Calling It Now
title: Calling It Now
body:
The Iron Spider suit is only used for the first 15 minutes and then we’ll never see it again….which just sucks.

The Homecoming suit is only used because May put it in Peter’s suitcase after Peter decided that Spider-Man is not coming with him on vacation. The suit will be destroyed in some fashion, symbolic of the end of his reliance on Tony.

The SHIELD suit is used so that it isn’t too obvious that Spider-Man is involved….which is fucking stupid since no one else can run up walls and web people up.

The black-and-red variant Stark Suit is actually the first Parker-made suit Peter makes after he has ‘a step-up hero moment’. Happy Hogan brings Peter to a workshop Tony left Peter in his will.
